TestAssertEqualsOmitsMessageWhenNotInStepText
/ Drift case 2 — the load-bearing reason this branch exists.
/
/ Step text `- assert %message% equals 'hello plang'` carries no custom error
/ message. With os/system/modules/assert/module.notes.md saying "omit Message
/ from parameters and from formal unless the step text names a custom error
/ message; Expected is taken from the step text literal", the LLM should emit:
/   parameters: { Expected: 'hello plang', Actual: %message% }   (no Message key)
/   formal contains Expected='hello plang' and no Message=...
/   formal and parameters agree on Expected ('hello plang', not %!data%).
/
/ Pre-fix shape that this test forbids:
/   any Message key in parameters duplicating Expected            -- forbidden
/   Message='hello plang' in formal                               -- forbidden
/   formal='assert.equals(Expected=%!data%, ...)' (disagrees)     -- forbidden
/
/ Non-determinism: real LLM + cache. Verification (architect's rule):
/ pass 3 fresh-cache builds in a row. See the sibling drift case for the
/ clean-rebuild incantation; same trap applies here.
- throw "not implemented"
